  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nRight now the decoder doesn't support any finer resolution than decoding a full variable, which can be a problem for giant arrays.  To better support partial decoding and pagination, the decoder should:\r\n\r\n1. Have methods to get variable names and types without decoding;\r\n2. Support decoding just part of a given struct/array/mapping.  Maybe it could even support slicing?  That might be a separate thing later.\r\n\r\nThis could also possibly be added in the debugger?  We'd need to figure that out.",
